io.branch.referral

Class ServerRequestQueue

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.branch.referral.ServerRequestQueue

  • public class ServerRequestQueue
extends java.lang.Object

    The Branch SDK can queue up requests whilst it is waiting for initialization of a session to complete. This allows you to start sending requests to the Branch API as soon as your app is opened.

      • peek

      • peekAt

        public ServerRequest peekAt(int index)

        Gets the queued ServerRequest object at position with index specified in the supplied parameter, within the queue. Like peek(), the item is not removed from the queue.

        Parameters:
        index - An Integer that specifies the position within the queue from which to pull the ServerRequest object.
        Returns:
        The ServerRequest object at the specified index. Returns null if no request exists at that position, or if the index supplied is not valid, for instance if getSize() is 6 and index 6 is called.

      • insert

        public void insert(ServerRequest request,
                   int index)

        As the method name implies, inserts a ServerRequest into the queue at the index position specified.

        Parameters:
        request - The ServerRequest to insert into the queue.
        index - An Integer value specifying the index at which to insert the supplied ServerRequest object. Fails silently if the index supplied is invalid.

      • removeAt

        public ServerRequest removeAt(int index)

        As the method name implies, removes the ServerRequest object, at the position indicated by the Integer parameter supplied.

        Parameters:
        index - An Integer value specifying the index at which to insert the supplied ServerRequest object. Fails silently if the index supplied is invalid.
        Returns:
        The ServerRequest object being removed.

      • containsClose

        public boolean containsClose()

        Determines whether the queue contains a session/app close request.

      • containsInstallOrOpen

        tag - A String value.
        networkCount - An Integer value that indicates whether or not to insert the request at the front of the queue or not.
